      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SWEET ON LEXY (3) was a beaten favourite here last start but came from much wider so did well for a 3.5m third. Tackled the Riverina Championships series prior where he won a heat. The better draw gives him the chance to atone. MAJOR ART NZ (5) broke through two back at Penrith then drew wider than this and worked but fought on for second at this circuit and distance last week. Has been quite reliable since arriving from NZ and should make an impact again. GOLDEN TRIBE (6) led from the outside barrier and faded last week but was good in placing in his previous two outings here. Strikes at 50 per cent at this distance so he is worth another chance. FRANCO NOVELIST NZ (4) showed improvement for fourth from a wider draw here last week. Races well third-up so can progress further. RED SAPPHIRE (7) has been ticking along well including a fourth from a similar barrier last week. Worth including.",
